\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.78,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.72,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.78,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.77,\n      \"feedback\": \"Variant of P3 using Miller-Urey atmospheric source instead of hydrothermal formate. Same concern about rxn_009 lacking experimental verification. Mixing atmospheric Miller-Urey products with hydrothermal formate is environmentally complex\u2014the formate transport to surface is not explicitly addressed. Slightly less coherent than P3 due to mixed sourcing.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Clarify how hydrothermal formate reaches surface environment\", \"Consider whether surface evaporite conditions could drive the coupling\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.90,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.70,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.92\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.85,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.87,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.88,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.90,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.87,\n      \"feedback\": \"Excellent pathway grounded in Chimiak et al. (2024). The reductive amination of glyoxylate on ferroan brucite (rxn_010) is experimentally demonstrated with ~52-69% yields. The glyoxylate sourcing via formose aldol + UV photooxidation (rxn_013, rxn_014) is plausible and creates a nice surface\u2192hydrothermal environmental flow. NH\u2083 availability is assumed but justified by alkaline vent conditions. The formaldehyde dimerization to glycolaldehyde is well-known formose chemistry.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Specify UV wavelength range for rxn_014\", \"Note that Chimiak et al. found ~97% of glycine was mineral-bound\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_sco